---
/**
 * PrivacyNotice — a calm, reassuring banner about the local-first posture.
 *
 * Works on My Resume parses Markdown entirely in the browser. This banner
 * states that plainly so users know their resume content is not uploaded,
 * stored, or transmitted. Tone: reassuring, not alarming.
 */
---

<aside class="privacy-notice" aria-label="Privacy notice">
  <svg
    class="privacy-notice__icon"
    width="18"
    height="18"
    viewBox="0 0 24 24"
    fill="none"
    stroke="currentColor"
    stroke-width="2"
    stroke-linecap="round"
    stroke-linejoin="round"
    aria-hidden="true"
  >
    <path d="M12 22s8-4 8-10V5l-8-3-8 3v7c0 6 8 10 8 10z"></path>
    <path d="m9 12 2 2 4-4"></path>
  </svg>
  <p>
    <strong>Your resume stays on your device.</strong> Uploaded resumes are processed locally in your
    browser. This site does not upload, store, or transmit resume content.
  </p>
</aside>
